message.content:
Analysis of the Target Structure  
• Block Count & Layers  
  – There are 8 total blocks arranged in 6 vertical “layers”:  
    1) A single yellow rectangular plank on the bottom.  
    2) Two tall green rectangular prisms standing side by side.  
    3) Another yellow plank bridging those two green blocks.  
    4) Two vertical orange cylinders on top.  
    5) A third yellow plank across the two cylinders.  
    6) A single orange wedge (roof‐shaped) at the very top.  

• Spatial Relationships  
  – Bottom layer: one horizontal yellow block spans the floor.  
  – Second layer: two green blocks stand vertically on the left and right edges of the bottom plank.  
  – Third layer: another yellow plank sits on top of, and bridges across, the two green uprights.  
  – Fourth layer: two orange cylinders (vertical) are placed on the left and right ends of that middle yellow plank.  
  – Fifth layer: a third horizontal yellow plank rests across the two vertical cylinders.  
  – Topmost layer: an orange wedge is centered on the top plank, forming a “roof.”  

Selection of Required Blocks from the Dictionary  
• Yellow horizontal plank → Dictionary index 6  
• Green vertical prism → Dictionary index 3  
• Orange vertical cylinder → Dictionary index 9  
• Orange wedge (roof orientation) → Dictionary index 11  

You will need:  
• Three copies of index 6 (for the three yellow planks)  
• Two copies of index 3 (for the two green uprights)  
• Two copies of index 9 (for the orange cylinders)  
• One copy of index 11 (for the roof wedge)  

Assembly Order  
{  
  Step1: Move block with index 6    // bottom yellow plank  
  Step2: Move block with index 3    // left green upright  
  Step3: Move block with index 3    // right green upright  
  Step4: Move block with index 6    // middle yellow plank  
  Step5: Move block with index 9    // left orange cylinder  
  Step6: Move block with index 9    // right orange cylinder  
  Step7: Move block with index 6    // top yellow plank  
  Step8: Move block with index 11   // orange roof wedge  
}
